node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: What happens when you cross @dantenewyorkcity's beloved Garibaldi with the quasi-tiki Jungle Bird? You're looking at it. The mashup cocktail, a tropical take on their signature Garibaldi made with Campari, Zucca Rabarbaro amaro, “fluffy” pineapple juice and lime, is "aperitiki" at its finest. While the drink is no longer on the menu at the New York City institution, you can always make it home. Get the recipe via the link in our bio. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro ⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 19, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: Keep it simple with a Gin Basil Smash. The herbaceous drink only calls for a few ingredients, but you're rewarded with a rich, complex cocktail. There's a reason why the aromatic green drink is ordered over 22,000 times a year at @barlelion in Hamburg, Germany. Get the recipe for @jrgmyr's modern classic via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

May be a cartoon of text that says 'BUHOTE A" Gragapa A Tropical Bar Meets Nightclub From the Mind of Sam Miller Take a tour of Great Escape, the San Francisco bartender's imaginary oasis where indoor waterfalls flow and tiki is more inclusive. story: PUNCH STAFF illustration: NICK HENSLEY'.

node.text:
What if your favorite bartender had free rein to create their perfect bar? Sam Miller's(@samson_miller) fantasy bar, Great Escape, has the heart of a high-volume “tropical cocktail lounge” and the soul of a dance-all-night club. Come for cocktail list—heavily influenced by tropical and Southeast Asian flavors, featuring a baby octopus-garnished Bloody Mary—and stay for the live Latin brass band hyping up the crowd in the monstera-lined oasis. ⁠
⁠
Head to the link in our profile, where with the help of @the.blend.us (#punchpartner), we bring Sam Miller's “fantasy bar” to life, considering every detail—from the vibe to the music to the most Instagrammable feature (and, of course, the drinks).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 18, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Welcome cooler temperatures with a Sundial. In this complex sour, @shannontebay builds on a Cognac base with cherry eau de vie, orgeat and small doses of elderflower liqueur and amaro, while an egg white and dose of lemon juice give it the characteristics of a traditional sour. The result is a frothy, rich, layered cocktail ideal for shorter days and longer nights. Check out the recipe via the link in our bio. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 18, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: If you're feeling the back-to-school blues, @dangbaum's Juicebox Cobbler might help. The grown-up play on fruit punch combines muddled pineapple, orange and lemon with passionfruit syrup and sweet vermouth. Served over pebbled ice and finished off with an over-the-top garnish, the recipe for this tropical take on the cobbler is available via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 17, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Banana, meet Boulevardier. 🍌 Though @anvilbitterbear's version reads a shade sweeter than the original, the banana lends a new richness and just a little funk, adding an air of intrigue to an old friend. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 17, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
The World’s Coldest Martini” is to the bar world what “The World’s Best Cup of Coffee” is to corner delis everywhere—a ubiquitous claim that’s rarely substantiated. Yet, ever since the accepted specs of the dry Martini began to crystallize in the early 20th century, the quest to serve it as cold as possible has persisted. At the newly opened @hawksmoornyc in New York, an ultrasonic jewelry cleaner and an insulated thermos produce an “aged” Martini that can be served in 30 seconds, at minus-12 degrees Celsius. “That first sip is really incredible, bracingly cold, just a wonderful temperature,” says bar director, ⁠
@adammontgomerie. Head to the link in our profile for @aarongoldfarb on the latest innovation in the endless quest for the coldest Martini. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 16, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: When's the last time you ordered a Blood and Sand? For many of you the answer is probably "never." But the time-honored classic does have some fervent fans in its corner. The formula for the OG—equal parts Scotch, Cherry Heering liqueur, orange juice and sweet vermouth—has its roots in metaphor; the red Cherry Heering is said to represent the “blood” and orange juice, the “sand.” Whether you want your cocktail to have anything to do with blood or sand is another question entirely, but if your curiosity is piqued, head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Is it too early for a Sazerac? Back in the day, we asked 14 of America's best bartenders to submit their finest recipe for the Sazerac—then blind-tasted them all to find the best of the best. node.text: @creativedrunk's Powerful Baritone reimagines the Penicillin as a stirred cocktail. Sticking with Scotch as the base, his play on the smoky and spicy modern classic is enhanced by floral Strega, herbal Becherovka and juicy Amaro Montenegro. Finished with a mist of peated Scotch, it's sure to cure what ails you. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch⁠ 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: "The Japanese Slipper—a simple sour built of equal parts, shaken, served up and garnished with a maraschino cherry—is exactly what a drink born in the ’80s should be: boozy, tart-sweet and unabashedly neon," @fredsiggins writes of the drink that unintentionally kicked off the cocktail revolution in Melbourne. With its carefree construction and lurid green hue, the icon of Australian drinking is back to claim its place in cocktail history. Head to the link in our bio for the story behind the highlighter-green drink. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro ⁠

node.text: PSA: There's officially only one week of summer left. Make the most of it with this ultra-refreshing, Spanish highball. The Rebujito, a simple combination of lemon-lime soda with fino or manzanilla sherry and ice, is easy to make and even easier to drink. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe and to read @suitcasewine on the history of the drink and the bartenders riffing on it today. 📷: @lizzieamunro
